gomodel:SYNGO_4011  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 2A, 2D: An analysis of baseline transmission in response to single action potential stimulation revealed that loss of MCTP function results in a significant deficit in presynaptic release. Indeed, altered baseline transmission and short-term plasticity can be observed in mctp mutants (Fig 5)\n\nFig 9. MCTP mutation does not result in a defect in the SV size, diameter or vesicle distance to T-bar or active zone length, and the defect indeed lies in SV exocytosis.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: Loss of MCTP does not lead to complete abrogation of synaptic vesicle exocytosis, but impacts the process. Based on this, the \"regulate\" box was ticked.. Experimental description: Drosophila stocks were raised at 25°C on standard food..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2345-393X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9888-0928" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4011" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7227" .

